{
  "stem": "1343.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was an interesting custom there in this small town that if there was a visitor in town, that everybody try to get him for the sabbath.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And whenever it happened that my father brought one home, and unlike here now, that I would have to ask [LAUGHS] my wife before I could bring somebody home, there it was an accepted fact of life, whether my father came home with one or with three.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was all well and all right.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then it especially became festive because if it so happened that that person was also [NON-ENGLISH], they used to discuss the Talmud.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And after dinner, this discussion went on and on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "One story brought along another that reminded him on the third.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And us small children just sitting there listening and finally [LAUGHS] almost falling asleep until our mother took us to sleep.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So memories like this really gave us strength to hope and survive.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we did, some of us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother was not only a very religious woman, but she was immensely well-read.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not only that, we had quite a sizable library of our own, but she went to the public library and read avidly.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Current, ancient, there was no subject really that one could not talk to her about.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This is not my impression only, but people that I met after the war told me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she also had the ability that when we went to sleep, she started to read books, stories, from us, from Anderson, from Grimm, and all those fables.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But later on, she started, when she felt that we're getting sleepy, she turned low the light and started to tell her own stories that she made up.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
